ly everyone could afford new items once they went mass. Earth&#8217;s curre=
nt inhabitants, by any historical standard, enjoyed incredible material abu=
ndance.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: =
26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">But weavers, printers, and raw mats were still p=
