6px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">She saw it immediately. Dev, as usual, was right.=
 Her idea was better because he&#8217;d rotated it, as she strengthened his=
 by remixing them. Once he&#8217;d said it out loud, it was so obvious.</p>=
<p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;">Modern tech was critical to making their ideas tangible, but the =
process itself, the training, was surprisingly unplugged. To come up with t=
he weirdest, freshest ideas, it almost had to be.&#160;</p><p style=3D"colo=
r: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Maya d=
idn&#8217;t stick to a strict regimen, but when she stepped back, she&#8217=
;d organized her whole life around the pursuit.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color:=
 #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">She ran =
every day like Murakami, lost herself in nature like da Vinci and van Gogh,=
 traveled widely and immersed herself in foreign cultures like Tarantino.&#=
160;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; mar=
gin: 0 0 20px 0;">She rarely drank, but when she did, she drank like Heming=
way, and she socialized widely, drawing inspiration from long-standing rela=
tionships with her co-conspirators like Woolf and Anderson.&#160;</p><p sty=
le=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px =
0;">She experimented &#8211; with her thoughts like Einstein and with her w=
hole being like Tesla &#8211; and meditated, like Rubin, Abramovi&#263;, Wa=
tson and a long line of thinkers who needed the space to think.</p><p style=
=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
">When she wanted to push further, weirder, she lucid dreamed like Dal&#237=
;, or tripped like Huxley and Jobs.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; fo=
nt-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Of course she read; =
she read mostly fiction, thirstily, like so many creatives before her. She =
let Geep summarize the latest non-fiction and research to her, tailored jus=
t so to the way she absorbed.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-siz=
e: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">She lived as rich and vari=
ed and as human a life as possible, so that she might generate ideas as ric=
h and varied and human as possible.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; fo=
nt-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Then she slept, eigh=
t hours every night, bone tired from a full day whenever possible, to give =
the fragments space to settle and grip, to wake up fresh and sit, quietly, =
in the early morning hours while fresh idea pinballs pinged, thwacked, bump=
ed, bopped, popped, whooped, zapped, plunked, blooped, plinked, flashed, zi=
pped, banged, and whooshed around her very human mind.&#160;</p><p style=3D=
"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">A=
nd then, of course, she pinged Dev, and together, they brought each others&=
#8217; ideas to life.&#160;</p><div style=3D"font-size: 16px; line-height: =
